import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="Species", y="Body_Mass__g_", data=data)
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of body mass across different species?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel("Species")
    ax.set_ylabel("Body Mass (g)")
    ax.axhline(y=data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Beak_Length__mm_', y='Sex', hue='Sex')
    plt.axvline(x=data['Beak_Length__mm_'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.title('How does beak length vary by sex?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
